column5: Congrats Jer very nice looking Ski just think how much fatter she will be in two months
Great fish Jer, Ill be a little further south this weekend lookin for the same, and some eyes as well, as my stock got a little depleted from last weekends outing
Fish of a lifetime!  Wow...you might've looked a little happier in the picture, think of all the people who'll end up seeing that pic
beauty. goes to show what catch and release can do.

I was actually fishing by myself and the lovely lady on shore who took the pics did a great job, but she caught me off guard in that one. I chose the one that best showed the fish.  Trust me I'm beaming inside!  Thanks for all the kind words from everyone!  Keep your hooks sharp!
Nice hold too.  That's how it is done people.
Thats right Glen,  Jer had a good upbringing and knows how to respect and treat a beautiful lady
Wow! That is an incredibly beautiful fish. Not many of the Kawartha strain get past 51.5 inches. Thanks for sharing.

I am having a hard time believing that is a Kawartha strain fish.  I do not doubt you got it in a Kawartha lake, but that looks like a Simcoe/ Trent/ Georgian Bay muskie to me.  Thick fish for sure.  Looks like it has October mass already.
Nice fish Jer.   Like I said, it's a good thing I didn't take you up on your offer this morning. That could have been my fish
great fish...congrats on the new pb
Great job landing swifty!  Now you can justify owning that huge net.
Nice fish Jer!  BTW, I just picked up my phone, yup, still has a dial tone...  Cheers, Ron...
Beauty fish Jer!! Good to see them growing that big in the Kawarthas...
That's no Kawartha eel....  River fish?
